rComments: Professor Roberts is a very clear communicator, though his more laid-back lectures can be occasionally dull. He has a firm grasp on the theory of urban studies and is generally approachable. A good, solid professor.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'So many papers']

rComments: An excellent professor, he made this one of my favourite courses. He is an engaging lecturer and knowledgable in his field. Grading criteria was very clear and the assignments, as well as the exam, were definitely fair. I feel like he cared about his students. I will definitely take another class with him if I get the chance

Very engaging lectures and the assignments were very fun to do. He was accessible outside of class and willing to answer any urban studies related questions students had like career opportunities, current social issues, etc. However the TAs for the course kinda didn't know what was going on and they were the people grading you

All of prof. Robert's classes have been awesome! He's a really enthusiastic lecturer and is really passionate about the material. I would definitely recommend any of his classes like JGI216! I always learn a lot and find his lectures very interesting. Very nice prof!

Great prof! His lectures are very interesting. He also gives students a 7 day grace period which is very helpful. Assignments are also fairly easy.  He is also very helpful to students. Would recommend his classes.

I would gladly take his class again! Lectures were very interesting and course material was applicable to real life and very compelling. Great guy! I learned so much from this class because he was so passionate about the material.
Really enjoy all his courses. Great asset to the Urban Studies department.
